{
  "rule": "weno5_advection_2d",
  "metric": "Linf",
  "expected_min_order": 4.5,
  "notes": "Classical Jiang-Shu (1996) WENO5 nonlinear reconstruction applied dimension-by-dimension on a uniform 2D structured Cartesian grid is theoretically O(h^5) in L_inf for smooth solutions (Shu 1998 §2.2; LeVeque 2002 §20). The 4.5 floor sub-5th formal order accounts for the small accuracy hit from the nonlinear-weight recovery of linear weights (omega_k -> d_k) at finite eps = 1e-6 plus the per-axis weight-transition coupling that lowers the asymptotic order vs the 1D fixture (which uses 4.7 — see weno5_advection/fixtures/convergence/expected.esm). Layer B currently SKIPs this fixture (input.esm declares applicable:false) pending an ESS extension that recurses mms_weno5_convergence into axes.x/axes.y; the 2D order is verified end-to-end via Layer C (fixtures/integration/cases.json, kind=weno5_2d_smooth_advection_convergence, threshold 4.4 across grid sizes {16,32,64,128})."
}
